    WHEN 592 THEN 'October ‘25 Investor Update: Quick update as we head into the remaining quarter of the year. We’ve sharpened our positioning and expanded our customer base, working with publicly traded companies — all while zeroing on becoming the best mobile QA solution out there. Below you’ll find recent progress since YC, learnings, our goals, and our asks :) Progress since YC: - In August we had ~$130K ARR, that is now ~$250K ARR with ~$2-2.5M in the pipeline. Working with teams like Fetch Rewards, YC mobile team, [solidcore], and Scribd and many more. - We''ve been doing a POC with DoorDash (~1 month in), which we hope to turn into a pilot ($15-20K/month), which when converted to a complete contract will have an ACV of $500K - $1M (estimate). - In the process of setting up pilots with AAA, 23andMe, Autonation and potentially Pinterest and Rocket Money. Each of these would be $250K-1M in ACV. Exploring if we would fit in heavily as an enterprise solution and maybe switching focus to that. Keeping growth momentum on both ends in the meantime. - Released an experimental caching feature, boosting agent speed by 5-8x per action (tap, swipe, enter text, etc.). - Brought on another engineer who we hope to join us full-time in December (extremely talented, amazing person, & wrapping up his last semester of college). Our team is now at 4 people (2 founders, 1 founding engineer, 1 part-time engineer)! - Cranking on growth: outbound, linkedin presence, case studies, GEO, podcasts, getting creative ...'
